New Artist's website for Cary Outis}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Background}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Cary has removed his existing website from the previous host. This was a purely html/css site I had written using DreamWeaver a few years ago. The host is poor and uses very old-fashioned software. }
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
New Site}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
For the new site, I suggest taking advantage of the back-office capabilities of Umbraco Content Management System. This will involve designing a number of "master" pages, including layout, appearance and behaviour. Cary will then format and add images and text to these pages, in other words "content", via the Umbraco back office.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
The domain name "caryoutis.com" has been re registered with }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.heartinternet.co.uk/" }{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\lang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Heart Internet}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
}}, so that Cary can keep full ownership of it, whoever is hosting the site. The site itself will be hosted with }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.footsword.com/" }{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\lang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
FootSword Technologies}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
}}.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Colours so Far}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
F9EEB0: Light Straw background (earthy, parchmenty)}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Black for boxes.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
4D3339: Aubergine for headers.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Font}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Cary's preference was for Andale Mono, which is a propietary Microsoft font, costing around $30. He has found an alternative on FontSqurrel, namely }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.fontsquirrel.com/fonts/shanti" }{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\lang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Shanti}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
}}. The Serif face for headers has not been decided.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Proposed Pages}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Paint, Sculpt, print, draw, workshops, biog., news, contact. }
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Home Page}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Cary Outis header in a nice serif font, probably chosen from }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.fontsquirrel.com/" }{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\lang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Font Squirrel}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
}}. Underneath that is a set of menu icons designed by Cary. These will correspond to artwork categories and also things such as Blog, About and so on.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Below that will be either a randomly accessed image or, if one is available and current, a news item. This means Cary will need a Rich Text editor to create news items for the front page and to give an expiry date for them.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Blog (or news)}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Will be taken from Cary's existing blog. The current idea is to use a link and make it appear more or less a part of the site. It would also be possible to import the entire blog into the Umbraco site and continue to write it from there.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Gallery Page}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
The format of the Gallery page will be based on the Google Images page. That is, as simple as possible. Rows of images will fill the screen size with a decent-sized margin around each. No frames. There is a suggestion that landscape and portrait images appear on separate (alternate) rows. All images in any one row will have the same height.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
A gallery page, for example, \'93painting\'94 will have a Cary-designed icon at the top, followed by a set of subheading icons, for example, \'93landscape\'94, \'93oil\'94. It might be best to generate these subheadings using tags on each image, so they can appear on more than one page. For example \'93oil\'94 contains \'93landscape\'94 and \'93nudes\'94, \'93landscape\'94 contains \'93painting\'94 and \'93ink drawing\'94.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
News/About Page}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
I have an additional sketch in my notebook and I'm not sure if this is supposed to be a front page or an "about" page. It could also be a "blog entry" page. At any rate, it contains a news box, a "blurb and pics" box, social media buttons and links. There is a request to have "blurb" on each page.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Social Media}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
At the very least on the front page, there should eb a row of social media buttons. There are a lot of social bookmarking sites! I have an account with }{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "http://www.addthis.com/" }{\fldrslt \cf2\ul\ulc0\langfe255\lang255\lang255\rtlch \ltrch\loch
AddThis}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
}}, who seem to offer a good range of buttons.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Links}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
I take this to refer to links to other sites. Possibly a separate page, on the about page and/or scattered throughout and where appropriate to the context.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Image Size and Shape}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Maximum of 2mb has been agreed. Also Max. 72dpi. This large format image will be used mostly for the lightbox, when a user clicks on an image or hovers over it. Exact dimensions will not be set, as it will depend on both size (small paintings vs large ones, also sculptures) and orientation (landscape/portrait). The default will be portrait but Cary will be able to specify landscape via a radio button. All images will be produced and uploaded by Cary.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Thumbnail image size. Yet to be decided but at any rate, these will be produced automatically by the back end software.}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
Cary would like the image to come in 3 sizes, thumbnail, rollover and the biggest, click on. }
\par \pard\plain \s2\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\sb240\sa120\keepn\i0\b0\hich\af3\langfe255\dbch\af4\afs28\lang255\ai\ab\loch\f2\fs28\lang255{\listtext\pard\plain  \tab}\ls1 \li576\ri0\lin576\rin0\fi-576{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Price}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120\langfe255\lang255\lang255\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
As yet undecided but not very much. I tend to charge \'a360 p/a for hosting but I think in this case that is not proposed.}
